  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Living Costs</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Hong Kong is extremely expensive. A comfortable lifestyle for a single professional requires HK$50,000-80,000/month; families need HK$100,000-200,000+ including housing, school fees, and insurance. Plan your capital accordingly—underfunding is a common reason businesses fail.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Generic Business Plans</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Immigration wants to see "why Hong Kong"—not a business that could operate anywhere. Demonstrate specific Hong Kong advantages: China access, regional hub role, financial infrastructure, or specific industry clusters. Generic plans suggesting Hong Kong is "just a convenient location" won't impress.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Ignoring Insurance Until Too Late</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Unlike some countries, Hong Kong public healthcare has years-long waits for non-emergency care. Don't arrive without insurance and expect to quickly arrange coverage—some policies have waiting periods, and gaps in coverage can be costly if you need care.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">CIES Real Estate Confusion</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Residential property does NOT count toward CIES's HK$30M investment requirement. Only non-residential property (commercial/industrial) qualifies, and even then there are restrictions. Many applicants waste time pursuing residential property investment assuming it qualifies.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Not Planning for Renewal</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Your initial visa is typically 1-2 years. Renewal requires showing your business is operating viably. Plan from day one: maintain proper accounts, generate revenue or show legitimate business activity, and keep documentation organized. Dormant companies struggle at renewal.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Healthcare in Hong Kong -->
  <section id="healthcare" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Healthcare in Hong Kong</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Hong Kong has a dual healthcare system: excellent but overcrowded public hospitals, and world-class but expensive private facilities. The vast majority of expats and business professionals rely on private healthcare with insurance coverage.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">The Hong Kong Healthcare System</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Public Healthcare (Hospital Authority)</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
          <li>• Available to HKID holders</li>
          <li>• Highly subsidized (HK$180/day inpatient)</li>
          <li>• Excellent trauma and emergency care</li>
          <li>• Specialist wait: months to years</li>
          <li>• Overcrowded wards</li>
          <li>• Language barrier possible</li>
          <li>• Queen Mary, Prince of Wales hospitals</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Private Healthcare</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• Immediate access, no waiting</li>
          <li>• English commonly spoken</li>
          <li>• Modern facilities, private rooms</li>
          <li>• Very expensive without insurance</li>
          <li>• Major insurers accepted</li>
          <li>• Matinée, Hong Kong Sanatorium, Canossa</li>
          <li>• Standard for business community</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Key Private Hospitals</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Hong Kong Island</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• Hong Kong Sanatorium & Hospital (Happy Valley)</li>
          <li>• Matilda International Hospital (The Peak)</li>
          <li>• Canossa Hospital (Mid-Levels)</li>
          <li>• Adventist Hospital (Stubbs Road)</li>
